TESTA pressed the pace two wide, took the lead near the five-sixteenths pole, led past the eighth pole and weakened late. JERRY'S TURN was up close four wide, bid in upper stretch and flattened out. DUNKLE failed to menace while racing four and five. SEDONA RED broke awkwardly and bumped at the start, saved ground off the pace and never threatened. COVERT KAT steadied along between foes around the first turn, raced two wide and lacked a closing bid. TEPPER raced off the pace three wide, edged closer four wide around the far turn appeared to clip PAPA JOJO'S heels nearing the quarter pole and lacked any further bids. LATE CALL was outrun inside. AWAY FROM HOME set the pace along the rail and gave way near the five-sixteenth pole. RACKET played no factor while racing three and four wide. AN OBJECTION LODGED BY THE RIDER OF TEPPER AGAINST THE WINNER FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE NEAR THE QUARTER POLE WAS NOT ALLOWED.
